messages.message:
does anyone know if this is a UI feature? I added a new audit log category, but it doesn't show up in the audit log type dropdown
(see project_operation_v2 on the left, but not in dropdown)

the UI calls `GET /api/v1/audit_logs` for the log types

search for `audit_log_query.get_log_types` in the codebase
you need to add the new log types to `_LOG_TYPE_MAP` in `shared-utils/py-utils/utils/src/py/instabase/audit_logs/audit_log_query.py`

so when I modify just that file, the typescript checks don't pass in an unrelated file...
